    "Niraparib inhibits PARP enzymes, addressing neurodegeneration by preventing metabolic impairment and regulating cell death 72.",
    "Empagliflozin, an SGLT2 inhibitor, regulates the insulin signaling pathway linking diabetes and AD 73.",
    "Doxercalciferol, a vitamin D analog, protects neurons against inflammation and oxidative stress 74.",
    "The clinical relevance of these drugs in AD treatment is also supported by their involvement in various stages of AD drug discovery, including literature review 75, epidemiological study 76, animal models 50,73, and human clinical trial (Phase II) 77, highlighting their potential effectiveness in treating AD.Moreover, t-SNE analysis has revealed the position of the five drugs in the lead combination mapped onto the biomedical embedding space (see Fig. 3 in \"Results\").",
